# Split large components (250 lines)

Keep route and feature components **under 250 lines** (excluding blank lines and comments). Split **before** merging when a file is at or above the limit, or when your change would push it past 250.

## When to split

- File is **≥ 250 lines** → refactor in the same PR (or split as a dedicated refactor if the user only asked for a small fix).
- File is **220–249 lines** and you are adding non-trivial UI or logic → extract first, then implement.
- User asks to extend a large file → prefer extraction over growing a monolith.

## What to extract (in order)

1. **Custom hooks** — form state, data fetching, derived state (`useReceiveItemForm.ts`, `usePurchaseOrderSelection.ts`).
2. **Presentational subcomponents** — sections of JSX with clear names (`ReceiveItemPoSelector.tsx`, `ReceiveItemDetailsGrid.tsx`).
3. **Pure helpers** — mapping, filters, formatters (`receive-item-utils.ts` in the same folder).
4. **Types/constants** — only when shared across multiple new files.

## File layout

Prefer a **feature folder** next to the route or parent:

```
manage-stocks/components/receive-item-tab/
  index.tsx              # thin shell: wiring + layout
  receive-item-po-fields.tsx
  receive-item-form-fields.tsx
  use-receive-item-form.ts
  receive-item-utils.ts
```

- Re-export the public entry from `index.tsx` if imports already point at the folder path.
- Match existing naming in the parent folder (`kebab-case` files, PascalCase components).
- Keep shared UI in `@/components/` only when used outside the feature.

## Rules for the split

- **No behavior change** unless the user asked for a feature fix in the same task.
- Parent owns orchestration; children receive props (avoid duplicating `useForm` unless a dedicated hook wraps it).
- Do not split into one-line files; each extracted unit should justify its file.
- After splitting, run lint on touched files.

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ receive-item-tab.tsx — 400+ lines (form, PO logic, dialog, helpers)

// ✅ receive-item-tab/index.tsx — ~80 lines
export function ReceiveItemTab(props: ReceiveItemTabProps) {
  const form = useReceiveItemForm(props);
  return (
    <form onSubmit={form.onSubmit}>
      <ReceiveItemPoFields {...form.po} />
      <ReceiveItemSearch {...form.item} />
      {form.selectedItem && <ReceiveItemDetailsGrid {...form.details} />}
    </form>
  );
}
```
